      <p>
        The Practitioners exists to close the gap between the promise of AI and its
        practical reality in the social impact sector. Too much of the conversation
        about AI is written for technologists and investors. We write for everyone
        else — the operators, organizers, and frontline workers who are quietly
        figuring out where these tools genuinely help.
      </p>

      <p>
        Each week we document a real use of AI in the field: who's using it, the
        problem it addresses, what it cost, what broke, and what changed as a result.
        We're interested in evidence over enthusiasm, and in being honest about the
        limits as much as the wins.
      </p>

      <p>
        Our readers are nonprofit operators, social enterprise leaders, and
        humanitarian workers. Our aim is to be the most useful, trustworthy guide to
        AI in practice for the people doing the hardest and most important work.
      </p>
    </div>
